This project focuses on detecting fraudulent credit card transactions using machine learning models. Fraud detection is a critical challenge because datasets are highly imbalanced — only a small fraction of transactions are fraudulent. The goal is to build models that can effectively identify fraud while minimizing false alarms.

⚙️ Models Used
🔹 Support Vector Classifier (SVC)  
Finds the optimal boundary (hyperplane) to separate fraud vs non‑fraud transactions. Works well with complex, high‑dimensional data.

🔹 Logistic Regression  
A simple yet effective baseline model that predicts the probability of fraud based on transaction features.


