Evaluation Metrics

Precision, Recall, F1‑Score, ROC‑AUC

Focus on Recall (catching frauds) and Precision (avoiding false positives)


💡 Key Insights
Logistic Regression provides a fast baseline and interpretable results.

SVC achieves better separation between fraud and non‑fraud but is more computationally expensive.

Evaluation shows that precision and recall are more meaningful than accuracy in fraud detection tasks.

🎯 Outcome
This project demonstrates how machine learning can be applied to financial datasets to detect fraudulent transactions. By comparing multiple models, we highlight the trade‑offs between simplicity, interpretability, and predictive power.
